  "text": "It has been argued that in complex situations it is necessary to go beyond the constraints of traditional scientific boundaries, such as the distinction between agency and structure, associated with attempts to identify discernible cause-effect linkages as definable answers to problems -and adopt alternative strategies. One alternative strategy is to surface the discrete second order relationships and patterns between, and within, systems that sustain the visible, first order descriptors and work towards ambiguous solutions by manipulating second order variables [CITATION_1] .",
